\title{Euclidean Domain}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-17}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{Dummit and Foote [[dummit-2004-abstract]] Section 8.1}


\p{An [[ra-000H]] #{R} is said to be a \define{Euclidean Domain} if there is a norm #{N\colon R\to\NN_{0}} such that for any two elements #{a,b\in R} with #{b\neq0}, there exists elements [the quotient] #{q\in R} and [the remainder] #{r\in R} such that
##{a=qb+r}
and
##{r=0\quad\mbox{or}\quad N(r)<N(b).}}